Mug cakes are the quickest desserts to prepare and today we make the Chocolate Atta Mug Cake which is simply the best thing ever🥰🤌🏻 Made with simple pantry ingredients, this super moist whole-wheat cake is like a warm hug you need after a long day at work and should be on your list, pronto 💁🏻‍♂️ Ingredients: 🍫2 tbsp castor sugar 🍫2 tbsp oil 🍫3 tbsp yogurt 🍫1 tbsp milk 🍫1/2 tsp vanilla extract 🍫3 tbsp atta 🍫1/2 tbsp cocoa powder 🍫1/8 tsp baking powder 🍫1/8 tsp baking soda For topping 🍫2 tbsp melted chocolate Method: 1. In a microwave safe mug start by adding castor sugar , oil , yogurt ,milk and vanilla extract. Mix till everything is combined. 2. Now add in all the dry ingredients-atta, cocoa powder, baking powder and baking soda in the mug. 3. Make sure to scrape the bottom and mix everything well. 4. Microwave the mug cake on regular heating mode for 2 minutes. 5. Once the cake is cooked completely, top it up with some dark melted chocolate and consume immediately. bake with shivesh, shivesh bhatia, mug cake, chocolate mug cake, eggless caking, easy cake recipes, chocolate cake, chocolate recipes, recipes, quick desserts, easy desserts, yummy, august, explore, baking, food, sweet tooth
